We have shown that there is a dynamically coherent extratropical
response to global warming, consistent with previous analyses,
involving a southeastward shift of the upper level winds, an
increase in storm track activity in the east Paciﬁc, and an increase
in CA moisture convergence. We have also shown that there is a
dynamically coherent tropical response, including an increase
in central/eastern tropical Paciﬁc divergence and a poleward
propagating Rossby wave. Both are reminiscent of an El Nin
teleconnection. CMIP5 models with higher correlation between CA
